==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dialytic
<hw>Di`a*lyt"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/.
See <er>Dialysis</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the quality of unloosing or
separating.</def> <rj><au>Clarke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dialytic telescope</b></col>, <cd>an achromatic telescope
in which the colored dispersion produced by a single object lens of
crown glass is corrected by a smaller concave lens, or combination of
lenses, of high dispersive power, placed at a distance in the narrower
part of the converging cone of rays, usually near the middle of the
tube.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dialyzate</ent>⟦br⟧
